No heels, no lingerie.
The essence of the great masters of flamenco, freed from all tensions to obtain the relaxed appearance of man or woman.
On the one hand, the artist.
On the other, the person.
Inseparable except in privacy, in these unknown moments of the general public, where one discovers intimate gestures and stolen looks of artists who do not care to go on stage.
The German G<0xC3><0xBC>nther Bauer mixes in "Flamenco - people" the theatricality of a few stagings with singers, dancers and guitarists with this lesser-known side of the artists.
In this project, the photographer takes up the particular iconography of flamenco from different angles.
Included in the Flamenco Photography Month programming, the exhibition "reflects the international importance of flamenco, bigger every day," explains the creator, who explains that "Flamenco - people" "can be anyone but, after seeing the photos, the observer realizes that these are not typified images.
