To capture moments of personality of these artists you do not have to take photos on stage.
They have a clean personality and character.
What interested me was creating an intimate atmosphere that allows me to capture with the camera the personality moments of the flamenco stars.”
With the festival "Chant populaire des Mines", Bauer began in 1997 a long journey to photograph singers, guitarists or dancers with a plate camera.
These are portraits that, thanks to the choice of camera and equipment, recalls classical photography.
The implementation of various stylistic means breaks with the classic side of the image, giving it a touch of modernity, this reflects the perception of flamenco according to Bauer: "A music with very traditional roots that evolves and surprises every day".
It is not about dancing or singing in and of itself, but about the personality and character of the artist who captivates the public with his art.
