Industrial export sales prices increased by 1.1 per cent compared to July 2008, while compared to the previous year, they decreased by 3.9 per cent.
As a result of fluctuations in domestic and export prices, industrial production prices increased by 0.7 per cent compared to the previous month, and by 3.2 per cent compared to the previous year.
Domestic industrial sales prices have only increased to a lesser extent: 0.1 per cent, compared to the previous month.
Internal sales prices in the processing industry sectors have only experienced a slight increase of the order of 0.1 per cent compared to July.
