Price reductions have occurred in the textile and textile production (2.5 per cent), as well as in the manufacturing of electrical machinery and appliances (0.3 per cent).
In other sectors of the processing industry, the price increase has changed between 0.6 per cent and 9.1 per cent.
Throughout the entire processing industry, prices have increased by 10.2 percent over the past year.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sectors exceeded 18.7 per cent in the previous year.
Among the domestic trade groups and according to the allocation of sectors, in August, it was the initiator sectors of investment profit that showed the most significant monthly price increase (0.7 per cent).
