David Nailey, a professor at the University of Western Ontario in London, recalls the risks of fruit juices, whether in boxes or fresh, if associated with the ingestion of certain drugs; during the 236th National Meeting of the American Chemical Society in progressing in Philadelphia, he throws a new juice alarm to the patient, sneezing at them, and sneezing at them.
